# The deploy kit is checked out on Linux and executed there. A CRLF line ending in a shell
# script makes the kernel look for an interpreter named "bash\r" and fail with "bad
# interpreter"; systemd is similarly unforgiving about unit files. Development happens on
# Windows, so pin these to LF regardless of the local core.autocrlf.
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.service   text eol=lf
